oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: George Bancroft
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Engraving of George Bancroft (1800-1891) seated in chair. One hand is resting on the table beside him. The table has books, a pen, and paper on it. A wall of books is in the background and several books are on the floor next to his feet.
American historian and diplomat. Served as U.S. Secretary of the Navy and established the Naval Academy at Annapolis in 1845.
